It's a Windows 0x80070057 error, but that doesn't give a lot to go on. I've found another ticket where a client was having this issue scanning a NAS device. It turned out to be their EPP, Carbon Black, blocking it. I believe you have CrowdStrike, and I know they really don't like exclusions, but it might be work looking at disabling it on the target server, PHX-FS01, as a test.

 

What kind of NAS device is PHX-FS01 (e.g. Nasuni, NetAPP, Dell Isilon, etc.)?

 

Regarding the INDIA File Server: please confirm that the NEA service account has permission to login as a service INC-FS02.IN.AEXP.COM. Ideally, the account should be a local admin on that file server.
